def: An order of Entomastraca, including many minute Crustacea, bothfreshwater and marine.
A small silver coin and money of account of Germany, worthabout two cents. It is not included in the new monetary system of theempire.
Based upon, or consisting of, an operation or operations; as,operative surgery.
The upper end of the rudderpost, to which the tiller isattashed.
The act of filling up, or the state of being filled up;fullness. [Obs.]
With the sails furled, and the helm lashed alee; -- applied toships in a storm. See Hull, n.
One of the divisions of Crinoidea found fossil in paleozoicrocks; pentremites. They are so named on account of their budlikeform.
One of the Trematodea. Also used adjectively.
Having at the bottom, or as a bottom; resting upon a bottom;grounded; -- mostly, in composition; as, sharp-bottomed; well-bottomed.
To lay out; to spread out; to display. [R.] Drayton.
